            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive</strong> <strong>oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Pat your<strong> sea bass fillet[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper and season the skin with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sea bass</strong>, skin side down and cook for 5 min, then flip the sea bass and cook for 1 min further or until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Transfer the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>sea bass </strong>to a plate and reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
